3. Product Architecture Overview — CareLink SmartSync™ Azure Astra Application
CareLink SmartSync™ Azure Astra Application is architected as a hybrid, session‑centric, safety‑first clinical system that deliberately spans device, edge, and cloud domains, while enforcing clear responsibility boundaries between them.
It is not a monolith, not a pure cloud app, and not a traditional locally bound programmer application.

3.1 Architectural Intent (Before Layers)
Before discussing layers, it’s critical to understand the intentional forces shaping this architecture:
Clinical safety overrides architectural elegance
Edge execution is mandatory for certain behaviors
Cloud services must never be on the critical path for safety
Every interaction must be attributable and auditable
Failures must resolve into safe, explainable states
The system must be evolvable under regulatory constraints
The product must feel familiar to clinicians
Platform services must be reused, not re‑implemented
No layer is allowed to “know too much”
Responsibility boundaries are enforced even when inconvenient
These forces explain why the architecture looks the way it does.

3.2 High‑Level Architectural Shape
At a conceptual level, SmartSync Astra consists of six cooperating architectural domains:
Implanted Device Domain (outside product control)
Clinical Edge / Programmer Domain
SmartSync Application Logic Domain
Orion Platform Services Domain
Azure Cloud Infrastructure Domain
Enterprise Integration Domain
Each domain exists because a different set of constraints dominates.

